+# Migration Phases And Legacy Properties
+
+This rule applies to every migrated legacy `Process` or `Operation` in this repository.
+It extends the existing SuiteCloud rules without replacing them.
+
+## Phase 1
+
+- Legacy properties that come from `ArmsServerConf.properties` must be registered in `k8s/properties.yaml`.
+- Do not add `ArmsServerConf.properties` keys to the main Kubernetes ConfigMap.
+- `k8s/properties.yaml` must contain only values that originate from `ArmsServerConf.properties`.
+- File storage must use Google Cloud Storage. Do not introduce local physical paths for business files.
+- Before adding or changing a GCS route, check `.claude_rules/GCS_ROUTES_INVENTORY.md`.
+- If a required GCS route is not already documented, stop the migration and request the exact value.
+- Scheduled legacy loops must be migrated to Spring `@Scheduled`.
+- Do not use Pub/Sub, `@Async`, `ExecutorService`, manual `Thread`, or infinite loops for Phase 1 polling processes unless a later phase explicitly changes the rule.
+- Firestore must only be used for `UpdateCedPadRucProcess` error tracking when a file is sent to the error bucket.
+- Database credentials remain in Kubernetes Secrets during this phase.
+- Do not create or update JPA entities, repositories, DTOs, projections, queries, or mappers unless the exact DDL of every involved table is available.
+
+## Phase 2
+
+- Pub/Sub can be introduced only when the upstream producer is identified and can publish a file-created event with the GCS object location.
+- A Pub/Sub design must keep the same domain use case as the scheduler so Phase 1 and Phase 2 share business behavior.
+- Topics and subscriptions must be created by IaC, not application code.
+- The GCS object location remains the source of truth for file state unless a specific architecture decision changes it.
+
+## Future Redis Phase
+
+Target parameter flow:
+
+```text
+Central Database
+        |
+        v
+Redis parameter cache
+        |
+        v
+Application parameter provider
+```
+
+Recommended extension points:
+
+- `ParameterProviderPort`: application-facing port for reading typed parameters.
+- `ParameterSourcePort`: source port for loading parameter snapshots from central storage.
+- `ParameterCachePort`: cache port for Redis get/set/evict operations with TTL.
+- `KubernetesPropertiesParameterProviderAdapter`: Phase 1 adapter backed by Spring configuration loaded from `properties.yaml`.
+- `RedisParameterProviderAdapter`: future adapter backed by Redis.
+- `CentralDatabaseParameterSourceAdapter`: future adapter that reads authoritative parameters from the central database.
+
+The application layer must depend on `ParameterProviderPort`, not directly on Redis, Kubernetes ConfigMaps, or `Environment`.
+
+## Future Secret Manager Phase
+
+- Database credentials currently remain in Kubernetes Secrets.
+- Do not migrate database credentials to GCP Secret Manager in Phase 1.
+- When this phase starts, use the project shared-library rules for `jlib-secretmanager`.
+- Do not add direct `jlib-kms` if it is already transitively provided by `jlib-secretmanager`.
+
+## Parameter Strategy Decision
+
+Alternatives considered:
+
+| Alternative | Advantages | Disadvantages |
+|---|---|---|
+| Keep legacy parameters in `application.yml` | Simple Spring binding; low implementation effort. | Mixes migrated legacy parameters with normal app config; harder future Redis migration; duplicates Kubernetes ownership. |
+| Keep legacy parameters in `k8s/properties.yaml` | Isolates `ArmsServerConf.properties`; aligns with the requested Redis migration path; keeps the main ConfigMap clean. | Requires explicit import or mount strategy when the application starts consuming the values. |
+| Use an abstraction from now | Application code becomes independent of the source; easier Redis replacement. | Adds interfaces before every migrated process needs dynamic parameters. |
+| Prepare Redis without implementing it | Avoids premature runtime dependencies; documents the target architecture. | Requires a later adapter implementation and migration task. |
+
+Decision for Phase 1:
+
+- Use `k8s/properties.yaml` as the authoritative Kubernetes registry for properties migrated from `ArmsServerConf.properties`.
+- Add application code against a parameter abstraction only when a migrated process actually consumes those parameters.
+- Do not add Redis dependencies or Redis runtime configuration in Phase 1.
+- Keep normal service configuration in `application*.yml` and the main ConfigMap only when it is not inherited from `ArmsServerConf.properties`.


